{
  "texts": [
    "For rare events, y = y rare contributes minimally to the sum, causing the model to not learn these rare patterns effectively, leading to overfitting on frequent patterns and underfitting on rare events.",
    "Sensitivity to outliersDNNs might not generalize well to extreme events if those events deviate significantly from the training data's distribution.",
    "Extreme events can be seen as outliers.",
    "The presence of these outliers can skew the model's training process, as the loss function becomes heavily influenced by these rare points, leading to overfitting on these specific instances and poor generalization.",
    "As in Eq. 8, If y i represents an extreme event, it can act as an outlier."
  ]
}